Package ohos.location

Interface LocatorCallback


  • public interface LocatorCallback
    Provides a callback interface for the system to report the device location.

    This class allows your application to obtain the location result reported by the system after the location service is initiated.

    Since:
    1
    See Also:
    Locator

      • onStatusChanged

        void onStatusChanged​(int type)
        Obtains the location service status after the location service is initiated.

        The location service status can be:

        • Locator.SESSION_START
        • Locator.SESSION_STOP
        Parameters:
        type - Indicates the location service status.
        Since:
        1
        See Also:
        Locator

      • onErrorReport

        void onErrorReport​(int type)
        Obtains the error that occurs during the location service process.

        The error can be:

        • Locator.ERROR_PERMISSION_NOT_GRANTED
        • Locator.ERROR_SWITCH_UNOPEN
        Parameters:
        type - Indicates the error type.
        Since:
        1
